1 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
2 25–102.
3 This title applies only in Montgomery County.
4 25–903.
5 (a) There is a Class BD–BWL license.
6 (b) The license authorizes the license holder to sell:
7 (1) beer and wine for on– or off–premises consumption; and
8 (2) liquor for on–premises consumption.
9 (c) As a prerequisite for the initial issuance of the license, the owner of the
10 establishment shall attest in a sworn statement that food will be available for sale for
11 on–premises consumption during the hours that alcoholic beverages are permitted to be
12 served.
13 (d) As a prerequisite for each renewal of the license, the owner of the
14 establishment shall attest in a sworn statement that food will be available for sale for
15 on–premises consumption during the hours that alcoholic beverages are permitted to be
16 served.
17 (e) The Board by regulation shall specify the type of food that is required to be
18 available for sale for on–premises consumption during the hours that alcoholic beverages
19 are permitted to be served.
20 (f) (1) A holder of a Class BD–BWL license:
21 [(1)] (I) may also hold a Class 7 micro–brewery license issued for a
22 location in the county; but
23 [(2)] (II) may not hold more than [one] TWO Class BD–BWL [license]
24 LICENSES.
25 (2) NOTWITHSTANDING SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, IF A
26 PERSON HOLDS MORE THAN ONE CLASS BD–BWL LICENSE, THE SECOND CLASS
27 BD–BWL LICENSE THAT IS ISSUED TO THE HOLDER AUTHORIZES THE HOLDER TO
28 SELL, ON THE PREMISES DESCRIBED IN THE SECOND LICENSE:
29 (I) BEER, WINE, AND LIQUOR FOR ON–PREMISES
30 CONSUMPTION; AND

HOUSE BILL 1174 3
1 (II) ONLY PRIVATE–LABEL PRODUCTS MANUFACTURED
2 EXCLUSIVELY FOR THE HOLDER FOR OFF–PREMISES CONSUMPTION.
3 (g) The annual license fee is $3,500.
4 25–1503.
5 Multiple licenses may be issued for the same premises or to an individual for the use
6 of that individual, a partnership, a corporation, an unincorporated association, or a limited
7 liability company if:
8 (1) (I) the licenses are Class H beer and wine licenses; and
9 [(2)] (II) each premises is a restaurant in a bowling establishment that
10 has at least 30 lanes with automatic pinsetters; OR
11 (2) THE LICENSES ARE CLASS BD–BWL LICENSES.
12 25–1614.
13 (a) Except as provided in § 25–1615 of this subtitle, the Board may not authorize
14 the same license holder to hold more than 10 licenses.
15 (b) The 10 licenses that may be held by the same license holder:
16 (1) may include:
17 (i) one or more Class H–BW licenses; and
18 (ii) one or more Class B–K licenses; and
19 (2) may not include more than [one] TWO Class BD–BWL [license]
20 LICENSES.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
22 1, 2025.

